#. Tag: para
#: security_ad_support.xml:16
#, no-c-format
msgid "&ad;* (&ada;) is a directory-service based on LDAP, Kerberos, and other services. It is used by Microsoft&thrdmrk; Windows&thrdmrk; to manage resources, services, and people. In a Microsoft Windows network, &ad; provides information about these objects, restricts access to them, and enforces policies. &productnamereg; lets you join existing &ad; domains and integrate your Linux machine into a Windows environment."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: security_ad_support.xml:26
#, no-c-format
msgid "Integrating Linux and &ad; environments"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: security_ad_support.xml:28
#, no-c-format
msgid "With a Linux client (configured as an &ad; client) that is joined to an existing &ad; domain, benefit from various features not available on a pure &productname; Linux client:"
