#. Tag: term
#: security_ad_support.xml:468
#, no-c-format
msgid "DNS"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: security_ad_support.xml:470
#, no-c-format
msgid "Configure your client machine to use a DNS server that can forward DNS requests to the &ad; DNS server. Alternatively, configure your machine to use the &ad; DNS server as the name service data source."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: security_ad_support.xml:478
#, no-c-format
msgid "NTP"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: security_ad_support.xml:480
#, no-c-format
msgid "To succeed with Kerberos authentication, the client must have its time set accurately. It is highly recommended to use a central NTP time server for this purpose (this can be also the NTP server running on your &ad; domain controller). If the clock skew between your Linux host and the domain controller exceeds a certain limit, Kerberos authentication fails and the client is logged in using the weaker NTLM (NT LAN Manager) authentication. For more details about using &ad; for time synchronization, see <xref linkend=\"proc-ad-join\"/> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: security_ad_support.xml:494
#, no-c-format
